						               													<description>Memoroute is a memory game which moles compete to open new underground paths. Unlike other memory games, you don't take two matching tiles, instead, your mole moves to a hole next to the matching tile that you opened secondly. Most of the times, you have to match several tile sets (and move your mole) until your mole finally reaches to a hole you are to connect.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On your turn, you select one of the face-down flower tiles adjacent to your mole pawn and flip it to the flower side, and then select another face-down flower tile from anywhere on the board. If the two tiles match, move your mole next to one of the holes adjacent to the second tile.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You keep having your turn until you fail to find two matching tiles. And in anytime during your turn, if your mole gets to a hole indicated on your mission card, you flip that card and continue your turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When you fail, you reset the game board by flipping all the opened tile and pass your turn.  When a player flips all four mission cards, the player wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Moles, moles! Find the holes and stick the poles!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
